{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"065f3b3b-eab2-41fe-9ec7-5c88c0db2790","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_YaOlwVAEx6oYRbrhM68aqm","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-b3286609a063450dbc70a70ff5c87a74/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-b3286609a063450dbc70a70ff5c87a74/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"2070cf76-772c-43b4-a951-e249f00c268c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference things defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. Currently the order is:\n\n1. Services.fs - references Domain types\n2. Domain.fs - defines the types\n3. Program.fs - references both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. So `Domain.fs` needs to come before `Services.fs`.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. Domain.fs\n2. Services.fs\n3. Program.fs","outputTokens":431,"requestId":"5C24:2F61F4:5D7AA52:664F5C7:69F155FF"},"id":"4503e580-aa8d-4665-9075-d6392ac016b9","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:51:19.104Z","parentId":"4f33790a-26be-41dc-8e33-ef11e25865c6"}
